      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "c873fe5a3623b114557b61633990122de90bd628",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-08-16 10:10:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThis has reduced the compilebench time somewhat, but did not affect the IOR times at all, which still run an hour each.\n\nI'm not sure why the last patch removed the reduction in IOR time from the previous one, but it seems like a waste to run IOR for 4h on NFS, when we don't run nearly that much IOR testing on native Lustre.  I think it makes sense to submit a follow-on patch that also reduces the IOR test time, like the earlier version of this patch did.\n\nNote: for the new patch, just use \"testgroup=parallel-scale-nfsv4\" instead of \"testgroup=full\", since this wastes a lot of testing time for no benefit related to this patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    }
  ],
